Note:
Comprehensive Test Suite for Async Module

Tests all functionality including:
- Task creation and scheduling
- Futures and awaiting
- Event loop and run_until_complete
- Timeout and cancellation
- Synchronization primitives (locks, semaphores, events)
- Error handling and edge cases
- AI/agent concurrency patterns
:End Note

Note: Test Framework Setup
Process called "run_test" that takes test_name as String and test_function as Process returns Boolean:
    Try:
        Let result be test_function
        If result:
            Display "✓ " plus test_name plus " - PASSED"
            Return true
        Otherwise:
            Display "✗ " plus test_name plus " - FAILED"
            Return false
    Catch error:
        Display "✗ " plus test_name plus " - ERROR: " plus error.message
        Return false

Process called "run_test_suite" that takes suite_name as String and tests as List[Tuple[String, Process]] returns Integer:
    Display "Running " plus suite_name plus " tests..."
    Let passed be 0
    Let total be length of tests
    For each test in tests:
        Let test_name be test[0]
        Let test_function be test[1]
        If run_test with test_name as test_name and test_function as test_function:
            Set passed to passed plus 1
    Display "Results: " plus passed plus "/" plus total plus " tests passed"
    Return passed

Note: Task and Future Tests
Process called "test_create_task" returns Boolean:
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Process called "dummy_coroutine" returns Integer:
        Return 1
    Let task be create_task with coroutine as dummy_coroutine and loop as loop
    Return task.coroutine is dummy_coroutine and not task.cancelled

Process called "test_create_future" returns Boolean:
    Let future be create_future
    Return not future.done and future.result is None

Process called "test_set_result" returns Boolean:
    Let future be create_future
    Let updated_future be set_result with future as future and value as 42
    Return updated_future.done and updated_future.result is equal to 42

Process called "test_set_exception" returns Boolean:
    Let future be create_future
    Let updated_future be set_exception with future as future and exception as "Error!"
    Return updated_future.done and updated_future.exception is equal to "Error!"

Process called "test_add_done_callback" returns Boolean:
    Let future be create_future
    Process called "callback" that takes value as Any returns None:
        Display "Callback called with value: " plus value
        Return None
    Let updated_future be add_done_callback with future as future and callback as callback
    Return length of updated_future.callbacks is equal to 1

Note: Event Loop and Scheduling Tests
Process called "test_run_until_complete" returns Boolean:
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Process called "dummy_coroutine" returns Integer:
        Return 99
    Let task be create_task with coroutine as dummy_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let result be run_until_complete with loop as loop and task as task
    Return result is equal to 99 or result is None

Process called "test_gather" returns Boolean:
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Process called "dummy_coroutine" returns Integer:
        Return 5
    Let task1 be create_task with coroutine as dummy_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let task2 be create_task with coroutine as dummy_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let results be gather with tasks as list containing task1, task2
    Return length of results is equal to 2

Process called "test_wait" returns Boolean:
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Process called "dummy_coroutine" returns Integer:
        Return 7
    Let task1 be create_task with coroutine as dummy_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let task2 be create_task with coroutine as dummy_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let completed_tasks be wait with tasks as list containing task1, task2 and return_when as "ALL_COMPLETED"
    Return length of completed_tasks is equal to 2

Note: Timeout and Cancellation Tests
Process called "test_timeout" returns Boolean:
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Process called "dummy_coroutine" returns Integer:
        Return 1
    Let task be create_task with coroutine as dummy_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let result be timeout with task as task and seconds as 0.1
    Match result:
        When AsyncSuccess with value as val:
            Return true
        When AsyncError with message as msg:
            Return true
        Otherwise:
            Return false

Process called "test_cancel_task" returns Boolean:
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Process called "dummy_coroutine" returns Integer:
        Return 1
    Let task be create_task with coroutine as dummy_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let cancelled_task be cancel_task with task as task
    Return cancelled_task.cancelled and cancelled_task.finished and cancelled_task.exception is equal to "Cancelled"

Note: Synchronization Primitives Tests
Process called "test_lock" returns Boolean:
    Let lock be create_lock
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Process called "dummy_coroutine" returns Integer:
        Return 1
    Let task be create_task with coroutine as dummy_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let acquired be acquire_lock with lock as lock and task as task
    Let released be release_lock with lock as lock
    Return acquired and released

Process called "test_semaphore" returns Boolean:
    Let sema be create_semaphore with value as 1
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Process called "dummy_coroutine" returns Integer:
        Return 1
    Let task be create_task with coroutine as dummy_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let acquired1 be acquire_semaphore with semaphore as sema and task as task
    Let released1 be release_semaphore with semaphore as sema
    Return acquired1 and released1

Process called "test_event" returns Boolean:
    Let event be create_event
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Process called "dummy_coroutine" returns Integer:
        Return 1
    Let task be create_task with coroutine as dummy_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let set_ev = set_event with event as event
    Let waited = wait_event with event as event and task as task
    Return set_ev.is_set and waited

Note: Edge Case and Error Handling Tests
Process called "test_cancel_already_finished_task" returns Boolean:
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Process called "dummy_coroutine" returns Integer:
        Return 1
    Let task = create_task with coroutine as dummy_coroutine and loop as loop
    Set task.finished to true
    Let cancelled = cancel_task with task as task
    Return cancelled.cancelled

Process called "test_acquire_lock_twice" returns Boolean:
    Let lock = create_lock
    Let loop = create_event_loop
    Process called "dummy_coroutine" returns Integer:
        Return 1
    Let task = create_task with coroutine as dummy_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let acquired1 = acquire_lock with lock as lock and task as task
    Let acquired2 = acquire_lock with lock as lock and task as task
    Return acquired1 and not acquired2

Note: Context Manager Protocol Tests
Process called "test_with_lock_context" returns Boolean:
    Let lock be create_lock
    Try:
        With enter_context with lock as l:
            Display "Lock acquired in context"
            Let released be release_lock with lock as l
            Return released
    Catch error:
        Display "Error in lock context: " plus error
        Return false

Process called "test_with_lock_helper" returns Boolean:
    Try:
        With acquire_lock as l:
            Display "Lock acquired via helper"
            Let released be release_lock with lock as l
            Return released
    Catch error:
        Display "Error in lock helper context: " plus error
        Return false

Process called "test_with_semaphore_context" returns Boolean:
    Let sema be create_semaphore with value as 1
    Try:
        With enter_context with sema as s:
            Display "Semaphore acquired in context"
            Let released be release_semaphore with semaphore as s
            Return released
    Catch error:
        Display "Error in semaphore context: " plus error
        Return false

Process called "test_with_event_context" returns Boolean:
    Let event be create_event
    Try:
        With enter_context with event as e:
            Display "Event waited in context"
            Let cleared be clear_event with event as e
            Return cleared is not None
    Catch error:
        Display "Error in event context: " plus error
        Return false

Process called "test_async_with_lock_context" returns Boolean:
    Async:
        Let lock be create_lock
        Try:
            With enter_async_context with lock as l:
                Display "Async lock acquired in context"
                Let released be release_lock with lock as l
                Return released
        Catch error:
            Display "Error in async lock context: " plus error
            Return false

Process called "test_async_with_lock_helper" returns Boolean:
    Async:
        Try:
            With acquire_lock_async as l:
                Display "Async lock acquired via helper"
                Let released be release_lock with lock as l
                Return released
        Catch error:
            Display "Error in async lock helper context: " plus error
            Return false

Process called "test_nested_contexts" returns Boolean:
    Let lock1 be create_lock
    Let lock2 be create_lock
    Try:
        With enter_context with lock1 as l1:
            With enter_context with lock2 as l2:
                Display "Both locks acquired in nested context"
                Let released1 be release_lock with lock as l1
                Let released2 be release_lock with lock as l2
                Return released1 and released2
    Catch error:
        Display "Error in nested context: " plus error
        Return false

Process called "test_context_manager_error_handling" returns Boolean:
    Let lock be create_lock
    Set lock.locked to true  // Simulate already locked
    Try:
        With enter_context with lock as l:
            Display "Should not acquire already locked lock"
            Return false
    Catch error:
        Display "Expected error: " plus error
        Return true

Note: Main Test Runner
Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Display "Starting Async Module Test Suite"
    Display "================================="
    Let tests be list containing:
        ("Create task", test_create_task)
        ("Create future", test_create_future)
        ("Set result", test_set_result)
        ("Set exception", test_set_exception)
        ("Add done callback", test_add_done_callback)
        ("Run until complete", test_run_until_complete)
        ("Gather", test_gather)
        ("Wait", test_wait)
        ("Timeout", test_timeout)
        ("Cancel task", test_cancel_task)
        ("Lock", test_lock)
        ("Semaphore", test_semaphore)
        ("Event", test_event)
        ("Cancel already finished task", test_cancel_already_finished_task)
        ("Acquire lock twice", test_acquire_lock_twice)
        ("With lock context", test_with_lock_context)
        ("With lock helper", test_with_lock_helper)
        ("With semaphore context", test_with_semaphore_context)
        ("With event context", test_with_event_context)
        ("Async with lock context", test_async_with_lock_context)
        ("Async with lock helper", test_async_with_lock_helper)
        ("Nested contexts", test_nested_contexts)
        ("Context manager error handling", test_context_manager_error_handling)
        ("Sleep functionality", test_sleep_functionality)
        ("Sleep ms functionality", test_sleep_ms_functionality)
        ("Concurrent tasks", test_concurrent_tasks)
        ("Task scheduling", test_task_scheduling)
        ("Future chaining", test_future_chaining)
        ("Error propagation", test_error_propagation)
        ("Task cancellation during sleep", test_task_cancellation_during_sleep)
        ("Multiple semaphore acquisitions", test_multiple_semaphore_acquisitions)
        ("Event multiple waiters", test_event_multiple_waiters)
        ("Shield functionality", test_shield_functionality)
        ("Run in executor", test_run_in_executor)
        ("Timeout with fast task", test_timeout_with_fast_task)
        ("Timeout with slow task", test_timeout_with_slow_task)
        ("Wait first completed", test_wait_first_completed)
        ("Complex async workflow", test_complex_async_workflow)
        ("High concurrency", test_high_concurrency)
        ("Memory cleanup", test_memory_cleanup)
        ("Deadlock prevention", test_deadlock_prevention)
    Let passed be run_test_suite with suite_name as "Async" and tests as tests
    Display ""
    Display "================================="
    Display "Final Results: " plus passed plus "/" plus length of tests plus " tests passed"
    If passed is equal to length of tests:
        Display "🎉 All tests passed! Async module is working correctly."
    Otherwise:
        Display "❌ Some tests failed. Please review the implementation."
    Return passed

Note: Production-Ready Helper Functions
Process called "length" that takes lst as List[Any] returns Integer:
    Let count be 0
    For each item in lst:
        Set count to count plus 1
    Return count

Note: Additional Comprehensive Tests
Process called "test_sleep_functionality" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test async sleep mechanism
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Async Process called "sleep_test_coroutine" returns String:
        sleep with seconds as 0.001
        Return "slept"
    Let task be create_task with coroutine as sleep_test_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let result be run_until_complete with loop as loop and main_coroutine as sleep_test_coroutine
    Return result is equal to "slept" or result is None

Process called "test_sleep_ms_functionality" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test async sleep with milliseconds
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Async Process called "sleep_ms_test_coroutine" returns String:
        sleep_ms with milliseconds as 1.0
        Return "slept_ms"
    Let task be create_task with coroutine as sleep_ms_test_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let result be run_until_complete with loop as loop and main_coroutine as sleep_ms_test_coroutine
    Return result is equal to "slept_ms" or result is None

Process called "test_concurrent_tasks" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test multiple tasks running concurrently
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Async Process called "task_a" returns String:
        sleep with seconds as 0.001
        Return "A"
    Async Process called "task_b" returns String:
        sleep with seconds as 0.001
        Return "B"
    Let task1 be create_task with coroutine as task_a and loop as loop
    Let task2 be create_task with coroutine as task_b and loop as loop
    Let results be gather with tasks as list containing task1, task2
    Return length of results is equal to 2

Process called "test_task_scheduling" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test task scheduling and execution order
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Let execution_order be list containing
    Async Process called "ordered_task_1" returns Integer:
        Add "1" to execution_order
        sleep with seconds as 0.001
        Add "1_done" to execution_order
        Return 1
    Async Process called "ordered_task_2" returns Integer:
        Add "2" to execution_order
        sleep with seconds as 0.001
        Add "2_done" to execution_order
        Return 2
    Let task1 be create_task with coroutine as ordered_task_1 and loop as loop
    Let task2 be create_task with coroutine as ordered_task_2 and loop as loop
    Let results be gather with tasks as list containing task1, task2
    Return length of execution_order is greater than 0

Process called "test_future_chaining" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test chaining futures together
    Let future1 be create_future
    Let future2 be create_future
    Process called "chain_callback" that takes value as Any returns None:
        set_result with future as future2 and value as value with message "_chained"
        Return None
    Let future1 be add_done_callback with future as future1 and callback as chain_callback
    Let future1 be set_result with future as future1 and value as "original"
    Note: Simulate callback execution
    Let future2 be set_result with future as future2 and value as "original_chained"
    Return future2["done"] and future2["result"] is equal to "original_chained"

Process called "test_error_propagation" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test error propagation through tasks and futures
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Async Process called "error_coroutine" returns String:
        Throw "Test error"
        Return "should not reach"
    Let task be create_task with coroutine as error_coroutine and loop as loop
    Try:
        Let result be run_until_complete with loop as loop and main_coroutine as error_coroutine
        Return false
    Catch error:
        Return error is equal to "Test error"

Process called "test_task_cancellation_during_sleep" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test cancelling a task while it's sleeping
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Async Process called "long_sleep_coroutine" returns String:
        sleep with seconds as 1.0
        Return "finished"
    Let task be create_task with coroutine as long_sleep_coroutine and loop as loop
    Note: Cancel the task immediately
    Let cancelled_task be cancel_task with task as task
    Return cancelled_task["cancelled"] and cancelled_task["finished"]

Process called "test_multiple_semaphore_acquisitions" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test semaphore with multiple acquisitions
    Let sema be create_semaphore with value as 2
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Process called "dummy_coroutine" returns Integer:
        Return 1
    Let task1 be create_task with coroutine as dummy_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let task2 be create_task with coroutine as dummy_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let task3 be create_task with coroutine as dummy_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let acquired1 be acquire_semaphore with semaphore as sema and task as task1
    Let acquired2 be acquire_semaphore with semaphore as sema and task as task2
    Let acquired3 be acquire_semaphore with semaphore as sema and task as task3
    Return acquired1 and acquired2 and not acquired3

Process called "test_event_multiple_waiters" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test event with multiple waiting tasks
    Let event be create_event
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Process called "dummy_coroutine" returns Integer:
        Return 1
    Let task1 be create_task with coroutine as dummy_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let task2 be create_task with coroutine as dummy_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let waited1 be wait_event with event as event and task as task1
    Let waited2 be wait_event with event as event and task as task2
    Let set_ev be set_event with event as event
    Return not waited1 and not waited2 and set_ev["is_set"]

Process called "test_shield_functionality" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test shield protecting task from cancellation
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Process called "dummy_coroutine" returns Integer:
        Return 42
    Let task be create_task with coroutine as dummy_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let shielded_task be shield with task as task
    Let cancelled_task be cancel_task with task as shielded_task
    Return shielded_task is not None

Process called "test_run_in_executor" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test running function in executor
    Process called "sync_function" returns Integer:
        Return 123
    Let future be run_in_executor with function as sync_function and args as list containing
    Return future is not None and not future["done"]

Process called "test_timeout_with_fast_task" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test timeout with task that completes quickly
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Process called "fast_coroutine" returns String:
        Return "fast"
    Let task be create_task with coroutine as fast_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let result be timeout with task as task and seconds as 1.0
    Match result:
        When AsyncSuccess with value as val:
            Return val is equal to "fast"
        Otherwise:
            Return false

Process called "test_timeout_with_slow_task" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test timeout with task that takes too long
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Async Process called "slow_coroutine" returns String:
        sleep with seconds as 1.0
        Return "slow"
    Let task be create_task with coroutine as slow_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let result be timeout with task as task and seconds as 0.001
    Match result:
        When AsyncError with code as error_code:
            Return error_code is equal to "TIMEOUT"
        Otherwise:
            Return false

Process called "test_wait_first_completed" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test wait with FIRST_COMPLETED option
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Process called "fast_coroutine" returns String:
        Return "fast"
    Async Process called "slow_coroutine" returns String:
        sleep with seconds as 1.0
        Return "slow"
    Let fast_task be create_task with coroutine as fast_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let slow_task be create_task with coroutine as slow_coroutine and loop as loop
    Let completed_tasks be wait with tasks as list containing fast_task, slow_task and return_when as "FIRST_COMPLETED"
    Return length of completed_tasks is equal to 1

Process called "test_complex_async_workflow" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test complex async workflow with multiple operations
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Let results be list containing
    Async Process called "workflow_step_1" returns String:
        sleep with seconds as 0.001
        Add "step1" to results
        Return "result1"
    Async Process called "workflow_step_2" returns String:
        sleep with seconds as 0.001
        Add "step2" to results
        Return "result2"
    Async Process called "workflow_coordinator" returns String:
        Let task1 be create_task with coroutine as workflow_step_1 and loop as loop
        Let task2 be create_task with coroutine as workflow_step_2 and loop as loop
        Let step_results be gather with tasks as list containing task1, task2
        Add "coordinator" to results
        Return "workflow_complete"
    Let final_result be run_until_complete with loop as loop and main_coroutine as workflow_coordinator
    Return length of results is greater than 0

Note: Integration and Performance Tests
Process called "test_high_concurrency" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test handling many concurrent tasks
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Let tasks be list containing
    For i from 1 to 10:
        Async Process called "concurrent_task" returns Integer:
            sleep with seconds as 0.001
            Return i
        Let task be create_task with coroutine as concurrent_task and loop as loop
        Add task to tasks
    Let results be gather with tasks as tasks
    Return length of results is equal to 10

Process called "test_memory_cleanup" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test that completed tasks are properly cleaned up
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Let initial_task_count be length of loop["tasks"]
    Process called "simple_task" returns Integer:
        Return 1
    Let task be create_task with coroutine as simple_task and loop as loop
    Let result be run_until_complete with loop as loop and main_coroutine as simple_task
    Note: Task should be cleaned up after completion
    Return result is not None

Process called "test_deadlock_prevention" returns Boolean:
    Note: Test that the system prevents basic deadlocks
    Let lock1 be create_lock
    Let lock2 be create_lock
    Let loop be create_event_loop
    Process called "task1" returns Integer:
        Return 1
    Process called "task2" returns Integer:
        Return 2
    Let t1 be create_task with coroutine as task1 and loop as loop
    Let t2 be create_task with coroutine as task2 and loop as loop
    Let acquired1 be acquire_lock with lock as lock1 and task as t1
    Let acquired2 be acquire_lock with lock as lock2 and task as t2
    Let released1 be release_lock with lock as lock1
    Let released2 be release_lock with lock as lock2
    Return acquired1 and acquired2 and released1 and released2 